BRONVILLE cops in the Free State need the community’s assistance to solve a mysterious murder. This comes after a man’s body was found at Hani Park extension 19 on Wednesday. Police spokesman Captain Malebo Khosana said the body was found lying on the ground. “His face was covered in blood. On closer inspection, it was discovered he had an open wound on his head. “The victim was identified as Papi Stols and is estimated to be 32 years old. “No one has been arrested yet and the suspects are still at large,” said Khosana. The murder case has been assigned to detective Warrant Officer Gosiamo Pamla. Anyone with information should contact Pamla on 082 301 2821 or 057 910 9928. People may also contact the nearest cop shop or call CrimeStop at 08600 10111.